summary: SummaryL'Oreal Revitalift Triple Power Face and Neck Moisturizer SPF 30 is formulated with top derm-proven ingredients and now with broad spectrum SPF 30 to visibly reduce wrinkles and neck crepiness, firm face and jawline, & brighten.

reviews.headline: May not work for sensitive skin
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have sensitive skin and am pretty cautious in skincare. So the package is simple and clear. The texture is smooth but quite thick and hence its a little bit hard to apply throughout my face. Did not recommend for sensitive skin as I have a few acnes just after 2 days. 
However it does absorb quickly and leave my skin soft and moisture just at first use which impress me much. Gentle and nice scent.

reviews.headline: Repeat buyer
reviews.comments: This face cream is helping my lines in face smooth out.

reviews.headline: Great lightweight option with no white cast
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I usually prefer my SPF separate from my moisturizer.  However, for those looking to combine moisturizing with sun protection, this is a great option.  It is lightweight and absorbs well into my skin.  It also doesn't leave the dreaded white cast.  Overall, I would consider using it again.

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. My friend used this for me because my skin tends to be oily so I try not to put moisturizers on it. It breaks me out. She loves it though and she recommends it! So I would use this if you like to use this type of product.

reviews.headline: No watery eyes!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] It's a nice moisturizing feeling. Absorbs well. No pilling either on It's own, over products or under makeup. Not really scented that I can tell. I don't have to watch how close it goes to my eyes or they start watering like some other brands I've tried so that's nice. So far I don't notice any improvements in any fine lines. But you do need to use products for a good while before you will.

reviews.headline: Not bad but not my favorite.
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product is pretty decent.  I like that it has sun protection built in.  The scent was light and clean, but it did leave my skin feeling a little greasy, which is something I do not like. It came very well packaged.  I haven't noticed any breakouts with it yet so that's a positive.

reviews.headline: Need moreeee
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love when a good neck and face cream has spf in it. Don't have to add another step into skincare regime. The texture was creamy and felt nice on my skin. Make sure to be consistent to see results.

reviews.headline: Great under makeup!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I get sent a lot of products but at this stage in my life I need a product that is easy and I can easily apply. This item has now become a holy grail item. I love the scent, the texture and the way it makes my skin feel.

reviews.headline: Like
reviews.comments: I like this L'Oréal Paris triple power face and neck moisturizer spf 30. It has an interesting texture to it- it sinks right into the skin and doesn't leave too much of a greasy feeling.

reviews.headline: Best for the summer time dry skin
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love the way that this lotion made my skin feel. It was not heavy, but it has a very strong sense of sunscreen which I am not a huge fan of. But one nice thing is that it is convenient to be able to put that on my face and have it be light enough where I don't feel it. This was also extremely hydrating, but it didn't really help with the flakiness so if you have a very dry skin, I would not suggest it for you.

reviews.headline: This is nice
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] My mom seen i got this and wanted it 
So me being thoughtful & all was like well you have to let me know your thoughts on this , i recall giving her a small sample of it awhile ago & she loved that & this is way better 
She said the ingredients is perfect also the packaging too , the scent is mild & not noticeable , it's super effective too makes her face super soft & the texture is luxurious

reviews.headline: Effective but greasy
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Overall, this is a great product that I would still choose over many other moisturizers. But there's something about this particular product that I don't love. I can't tell if it's a film, or a greasiness that I'm detecting, but it takes longer than normal to soak into the skin and leaves me having to wait to apply makeup. I feel the protection and moisture it provides the skin are wonderful, which is why I give this 4 stars still, but it falls short due to the consistency in my eyes of being a product I love love. The scent is very faint and almost non-detectable, which I prefer for an all day moisturizer, and it seems to stay on the skin well even under makeup. It's just a little too "glowy" for my liking upon application.

reviews.headline: Don't think twice!!
reviews.comments: Definitely recommend especially if you have dry skin. This is so moisturizing and has improved my skin! The smell is very light and refreshing which is a big plus for me. This cream is not greasy and a little goes a long way.

reviews.headline: Good product just not for me
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love the ingredients in the product but unfortunately for me it does leave a white cast. The texture and consistency are nice and the scent is very mild. I won't be keeping this product but I would recommend for someone of a more fair complexion.

reviews.headline: Excellent moisturizer
reviews.comments: Excellent all-day moisturizer for combination skin. I also appreciate the extra sun protection, although I wouldn't use an SPF 30 without sunscreen. Absorbs well. Not too greasy.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I'm absolutely shook. I'll be the first to admit I'm a snob with skincare and feel like it should be fancy or expensive to be effective. I know it's not the case, but it's just something that was drilled in my brain. I've never considered purchasing moisturizer from the drugstore because I didn't feel like it would have much to offer. I also didn't think it would have the greatest ingredients. 

I got proven otherwise! After a week of this, my skin is in such a better place 🥲 Florida has been experiencing extra cold weather that my skin has never lived. It's extra dry and my current moisturizer would help for like 4 hours before I'd start feeling the dry skin again. This on the other hand, holy cow! One application in I was converted. My skin stayed plump for 2 whole fricken days! 

Pros:
•hydrates skin back to life
•literal visibly plumper skin 
•actual 48 hour hydration (yes, I tested it and can't believe I actually felt soft moisturized skin on day 2.)
•the price point! Anything under $50 for effective skincare is a steal. 
•accessibility! With so many drug stores and super centers around, I'll always be able to access this which is cool. 
•consistency is between thin and thick. It holds its shape when scooping and a little goes a long way but it spreads thin. There's a slick to it but it's not oily.
•sun protection! It's so so important and spf 30 is great for day to day.

Cons:
•I broke out after my first application, which was expected since this is new to me, however that one time was it. 
•the packaging is bulky and heavy. 
•no spatula! I greatly dislike dipping my fingers in cream and contaminating everything. I have spatulas because of my makeup kit, but it would be nice to have one included. Maybe in the actual design of the lid? That would be thoughtful. 

I would totally repurchase this and I'm actually going to add it to my kit. I can see this working beautifully to prep dehydrated skin. If you're curious or considering it, I highly recommend. It's definitely worth it.
faceoff_positive.headline: New drugstore staple

faceoff_negative.comments:
I was thrilled to try this product, especially since I'm a big fan of using products with SPF and need the hydration during the cold winter months. However, the instructions say to reapply every two hours, which I find a bit restrictive. Since I usually wear a day cream under my makeup, I'm guessing that means I'd only have SPF protection for the first two hours of the day. Despite this, I was still excited to give it a try.

Initially, the product felt fine on my face, but throughout the day, my skin started to feel tight, and my lips began to burn. By the time I got back home and washed my face, the skin around my mouth was bright red and itchy. This reaction was the only new product in my routine.

Since then, the skin around my mouth has developed a sunburn-like appearance, has started to scab and flake. I have given it a two star rating but I'm confident that this product can work well for others. I believe I just had a reaction to it which is unusual because I've never had an allergic reaction to a skincare product before. I'll have to examine the active ingredients and compare them to my usual skincare products to determine the cause of this reaction.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not For Me but Might Work Well for Others.
